Stroman and John Weidman, creators of ``Contact,'' a dance-theater
piece that opened Oct. 7 the Mitzi E. Newhouse Theater in Lincoln
Center. How the unconventional production came to life turns out to
be a surprisingly untortured tale of making theater, a process
often hindered by internecine politics and creative differences.
(Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) NEW YORK -- Oct. 17, 1999 -- DANCE-PLAY-1, 10-17 --
Deborah Yates and Boyd Gaines in ``Contact,'' a dance play created
by Susan Stroman and John Weidman. The production demonstrates that
in an age of corporate theater ownership and risk-averse
mega-musicals, it is still possible to create a small gem that
proves to be incandescent. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
