Joseph O'Neill. Perhaps it's a simple matter of an actor who hasn't
been told when to back off, but Rogers pushes so hard in ``Look
Back'' that the play seems to cower in the corner whenever he
enters. (Michelle V. Agins/New York Times Photo)
</P>
