<P>
   TECH-GADGETS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ It's getting cheaper to carry
around a miniature digital recording studio. New Jersey-based Sharp
Electronics Corp. has introduced a personal MiniDisc
player/recorder that the company says is the first of its kind to
retail for less than $200. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TECH-CENTERPIECE-ETAILING_ WASHINGTON _ For retailers, the
holiday shopping season is the crucial period of the year when
their decisions about inventory, staffing, pricing and advertising
will result in drinking champagne in January _ or bathing in red
ink. (Geewax, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ Most of what you do on the Internet at home works
fine at the speeds you get from an old-fashioned telephone line
modem. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TECH-TOOLS _ Software reviews. This week: The Call Waiting Modem
from Actiontec works really well. (Warner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETWATCH _ What's new on the Web. This week: MP3.com offers best
in unsigned artists through new deal. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   CYBERSCENE _ This column will not move this week. (Husted,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TECH-MEDIA _ What the tech magazines are writing about. (Haddad,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
