<P>
   NUTRITION _ ATLANTA _ Daily story or brief out of the American
Dietetic Association meeting in Atlanta. (Kennedy, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH-CONSUMER _ If you had to find a specialist for a close
relative, which doctor would you choose? A new guide published by a
nonprofit organization may be able to help you. The organization
asked well-regarded doctors in their field which specialist they
would pick for their own relatives. It lists who's tops in their
field, by city and state. (Lore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH-MEDIA _ Health books on nutrition. Internet sites. Health
awareness month or week, plus phone number to call. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH-MOLD _ How to get rid of mold in your house. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   SYPHILIS-ROCKDALE _ CONYERS, Ga. _ Before May's Heritage High
shooting, an earlier scandal shook Rockdale County _ the diagnosis
of a cluster of syphilis cases among affluent teens less than 18
years old. In 1996, as Atlanta was preparing for the Olympics, 17
teens tested positive for syphilis, more than 200 were treated, and
about 50 acknowledged being part of a ring of kids who would meet
for group sex at each other's houses while parents were not around.
Tonight (Tuesday) a PBS Frontline documentary, ``The Lost Children
of Rockdale County,'' tells the story of the outbreak and talks to
many teens and some parents; it ultimately traces both the outbreak
and the school shooting to teen alienation, peer pressure and lack
of parental involvement. In advance of it, we talk to Rockdale
parents and teens, and community officials about the shock of
discovering the outbreak, the investigation of the cases and
reflect what health officials say are the lessons learned.
(McKenna, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SYPHILIS-FRONTLINE _ Review of Frontline's ``Lost Children of
Rockdale County.'' (Jubera, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
