   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Could one sum up an entire
life in 75 words? Can great stories be told, or arguments made with
such brevity? After all, 75 is a mere five words longer than the
Lord's Prayer. On the other hand, the Pledge of Allegiance is only
31 words. The secret of success would be to think in terms of pithy
but succinct. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
