that can send parents running for cover. As PBS prepares to air a
Frontline documentary that explores these topics by profiling a
Rockdale teen syphilis outbreak promoted by group-sex parties, we
offer some advice on opening a dialogue with teens about such tough
subjects. QA with Sarah Brown, director of the National Coalition
of Teenage Pregnancy Prevention, and a boxed list of resources,
