 Monday, Oct. 18, 1999     
 Editors      The Hearst News Service will file the following for
Tuesday. If you have questions, please call Susie McBee or Tim
Spence at 202-298-6920.    (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all
sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   VIEQUES-BOMBING (Washington) _ A Pentagon panel fails to produce
a plan that Puerto Ricans will accept to end a six-month standoff
between the Navy and the commonwealth over a bombing range on its
island of Vieques. The panel proposes resuming the bombing target
practice but at a reduced rate. It also calls for a phased Navy
withdrawal from the island and economic aid for the Puerto Ricans
who live there. The final decision on Vieques' future is up to
President Clinton. By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ First Lady Hillary Clinton's
campaign swing across New York this week highlights both her
problems and her advantages as a Senate candidate. She gets lots of
public attention, but it isn't all favorable. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
