<SLUG> BC-BC-KAN-BUDGET-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KANSAS CITY STAR BUDGET 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Tuesday,
Oct. 19. If you have any questions, please call The Star's News
Desk at (816) 234-4720.
</P>
<P>
   AMBER: The Amber Plan, which uses the media to alert a community
when a child has been abducted, is spreading across the country and
Kansas City is next. Police announced the plan here last Monday,
one day before Pamela Butler was kidnapped from her neighborhood in
Kansas City, Kan. There may even be a movement now to rename the
system here the Pamela Plan. Mary Sanchez. 40. Photo, graphic
</P>
<P>
   LEGIS: If Kansas City and St. Louis school districts lose their
state accreditation, expect a flurry of legislative proposals
designed to fix the districts to emerge in the General Assembly.
Kit Wagar. 25.
</P>
<P>
   SKEL: Ike Skelton helps land donations from private contractors
to help fund a multimillion-dollar military museum in Lexington,
Mo. Brian Burnes.
</P>
<P>
   CREME. Welcome to Creme de la Creme, a new nursery and preschool
in Leawood. It looks like nirvana for little kids. There's the
Beauty and the Beast soundtrack wafting throughout the
21,000-square-foot building, the Trike Autobahn on the manicured
playground outside, the model train rolling around a track near the
ceiling of the faux Victorian streetscape. And that's just the
trappings. Every 30 minutes, preschoolers are moved to a different
activity, from French to math to creative movement. Tuition runs
almost twice as high as the area average _ it's $12,000 a year for
preschoolers _ but satisfied parents say their children's happiness
is worth it. Yet child development experts warn that high cost does
not equal high quality. Kate Beem. Photo. 45.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS BUDGET OFFERS:
</P>
<P>
   EMOTE _ The emotional intelligence movement, one of the hottest
management techniques, is gaining some surprising converts in the
business community. By Diane Stafford. Photo, graphic.
</P>
<P>
   PUB _ The state of Missouri sues Publishers Clearing House
alleging the company used deceptive sweepstakes mailings to defraud
customers in the state. Paul Wenske
</P>
<P>
   PACERS _ Ellerbe Becket designs the new basketball arena for the
Indiana Pacers that will open in early November. Steve Everly.
Photo
</P>
<P>
   GOLD _ Gold Banc adopts a shareholder rights plan. Rick Alm
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS BUDGET OFFERS:
</P>
<P>
   ALCS. New York Yankees at Boston, Game 5, 7:15 p.m. Steve Rock.
16-18.
</P>
<P>
   WHIT. Jason Whitlock notes column.
</P>
<P>
   CHIEFS. Chiefs feature. Adam Teicher. Photos
</P>
</TEXT>
