<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Election'' _ Alexander Payne's dark comedy,
using high school life as a marvelous metaphor for American
politics, is one of the year's best films. Matthew Broderick, Reese
Witherspoon, and Chris Klein head the outstanding cast. Despite
terrific reviews, it had a lukewarm reception at the box office.
Don't miss the video version.
</P>
<P>
   ``Xiu Xiu: The Sent Down Girl'' _ Actress Joan Chen gets behind
the camera for this beautifully shot, compellingly acted tale of a
young girl growing up during China's Cultural Revolution. It's
subtle, affectionate, thoughtful, and tough. In Mandarin with
English subtitles.
</P>
<P>
   ``Frogs for Snakes'' _ Despite a solid cast, headed by Barbara
Hershey as an actress-turned-mobster, this is a pretentious, tired,
inside-showbiz yawner.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: Nora Ephron's romantic comedy ``Sleepless in
Seattle'' is given the full DVD treatment with a wide-screen
edition; commentary by Ephron and her sister, Delia Ephron, who
worked on the script; and a pleasant documentary about romance in
the movies. Too bad Emerson College grad Jeff Arch wasn't asked to
contribute. He came up with the original story and screenplay. The
discussions about building up Tom Hanks's character are
fascinating. . . . Mel Brooks's ``Young Frankenstein,'' in a
typical Brooksian move, is celebrating its ``25 1/2'' anniversary
with some great outtakes with stars Gene Wilder, Marty Feldman,
Teri Garr, and Madeline Kahn.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Oct. 19: ``The Wizard of Oz'' (remastered
and DVD), ``eXistenZ,'' ``The Nuttiest Nutcracker,'' ``Color of
Courage,'' ``Children of the Corn 6,'' ``Metroland,'' ``Life,'' ``A
Walk on the Moon.'' Oct. 26: ``The Blair Witch Project,''
``Tactical Assault,'' ``The Velocity of Gary,'' ``Hideous Kinky,''
``Arlington Road.'' Nov. 9: ``Life Is Beautiful'' (dubbed
English-language version), ``Instinct,'' ``The Castle,''
``Heaven,'' ``Break Up,'' ``Rogue Trader.'' Nov. 26: ``Wild Wild
West.''
</P>
</TEXT>
