A0672 &Cx1f; tad-z
u w BC-RECYCLE-CORRECTION18-     10-18 0103
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECYCLE-CORRECTION18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A recent article by Cox News Service erroneously reported that
the price of recycled polyethylene terephthalate plastic, or
``PET,'' is $7 a ton. In fact, PET, from which plastic soft drink
and beer bottles are made, is recycled at about 7 cents a pound, or
$140 a ton. The most recent price quotations for reycled aluminum
cans show they are bringing from 27 cents to 42 cents per pound, or
$540 to $840 a ton, in various markets.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
