   TIGUA-GAMBLING &QL;
</P>
<P>
   EL PASO, Texas _ In what was once a crumbling barrio on the edge
of El Paso, a small band of American Indians has defied the state
of Texas by erecting a 24-hour money machine called the Speaking
Rock Casino. The glittering gaming house, made of fake adobe and
decorated with Pueblo Indian motifs, reportedly brings in about $60
million per year. It is lifting the tribe of 1,200 Tiguas out of
poverty while making it a political force. By BARRY SHLACHTER.
Story will move in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
