   GLENNIE-PROFILE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED: Profile of Evelyn Glennie, Scottish percussionist who
is the heart of a growing legend. At the age of 8, growing up in
rural Scotland, an illness caused her to lose her hearing. Yet at
12, she had convinced herself, despite the skepticism of all around
her, that she wanted to be, not just a percussionist, but a solo
percussionist, which was virtually unheard of in classical music.
Glennie overcame her handicap to become what critics agree is one
of the finest instrumentalists in the world. She appears at Fort
Worth's Bass Hall on Tuesday. By TIM MADIGAN. Story will move in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MUST SEE-TV &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ We've been hearing about the breakdown of NBC's
steamroller Thursday-night lineup for a while now, the rap being
that it's tired, it's repetitive, it has outlived its brash
usefulness. True, all of it. But there's an alternative to
Thursday-night blahs: Tuesday. By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story will
move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
