<P>
   UNDATED _ Spending the past week in Los Angeles observing the
national AFL-CIO convention as it endorsed Al Gore for president
convinced me that organized labor has ended its three-decade
decline in political influence and may be on its way to being a
major player again _ not as strong as it once was, but stronger
than it has been. By JIM WRIGHT. Story will move in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
