   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   McCAIN-2000 (Washington) _ An influential early supporter of
Texas Gov. George W. Bush, former Rep. Guy Molinari of New York,
jumps ship to join the Republican presidential campaign of Arizona
Sen. John McCain. McMain, meanwhile, delivers a speech on the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty that Republicans in the Senate
rejected last week. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   DSP-CHIPS (Houston) _ Though DSP chips _ specialized types of
semiconductors that can be programmed _ have been around for a few
years and can be found in virtually every mobile telephone, they
are quickly finding their way into a host of new consumer products.
DSP is considered by Texas Instruments to be the processor that
will take consumers closer to the technology-rich world of ``Star
Trek,'' with such products as portable universal translators. By
TRICIA SERJU-HARRIS. (Photo available on NYT database.)
</P>
<P>
   BARLOW-COLUMN (Houston) _ The Beagle Brigade, dogs wearing green
coats, is being used to sniff out foreign plants and other animals
as travelers come through Bush Intercontinental Airport in Houston.
The U.S. Department of Agriculture estimates that these plant and
animal species cause about $140 billion a year in damage. By JIM
BARLOW.
</P>
