   MORALS _ WASHINGTON _ Modern studies have shown that damage to
the prefrontal cortex area of the brain can produce servere
impairments in social and moral decision-making in adults. Now,
scientists at the University of Iowa College of Medicine have found
evidence of even more profound ``moral damage'' in persons whose
brains were damaged in the prefrontal cortex as small children.
Persons injured as small children appear to have never been able
even to fully learn moral and social knowledge. (Nesmith, Cox News
Service)
