<P>
   SYPHILIS-ROCKDALE _ CONYERS, Ga. _ Before this year's Heritage
High shooting, an earlier scandal shook Rockdale County _ the
diagnosis of a cluster of syphilis cases among affluent teens less
than 18 years old. In 1996, as Atlanta was preparing for the
Olympics, 17 teens tested positive for syphilis, more than 200 were
treated, and about 50 acknowledged being part of a ring of kids who
would meet for group sex at each other's houses while parents were
not around. Tonight (Tuesday) a PBS Frontline documentary, ``The
Lost Children of Rockdale County,'' tells the story of the outbreak
and talks to many teens and some parents; it ultimately traces both
the outbreak and the school shooting to teen alienation, peer
pressure and lack of parental involvement. (McKenna, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
