<P>
   COCACOLA _ Coca-Cola marketing chief Charles Frenette is in New
York discussing the beverage company's latest marketing strategy.
(Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FED-INFLUENCE _ ATLANTA _ Jack Guynn, president of the Federal
Reserve Bank of Georgia, said Monday the influence of U.S. stock
prices on Fed policy has been overstated by market analysts.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOWDOW _ How far will it drop? That's the question among stock
market investors as they awaited the next round of inflation news
today. Some analysts forecast a drop in the Dow Jones industrial
average of as much as 15 percent, but market bulls challenge that
outlook on the basis of economic fundamentals and profit
expectations. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SBC _ AUSTIN, Texas _ SBC Communications Inc. announces it will
spend an additional $6 billion in its 13-state service area to
bring high- speed Digital Subscriber Line Internet service to 80
percent of its customers, or about 77 million people within three
years. (Ladendorf, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   GAPACIFIC-SUIT _ ATLANTA _ Georgia-Pacific has been hit with a
reverse discrimination suit by a white former employee of GP's
Palatka, Fla., mill. Joseph Green, a 32-year employee, alleges he
was unjustly fired in August 1998 to appease several black
employees who complained of racial problems at the plant. (Bond,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DELTA _Delta says it will buy Comair, Cincinnati-based commuter
airline, in a deal worth about $1.8 billion. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   w/DELTA-EARNINGS _ Delta reports earnings. As expected, the
airline's income is down 11 percent. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COMAIR _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Delta Air Lines will buy
Cincinnati-based Comair Holdings Inc., a major Delta feeder at
Dayton International Airport, under an agreement between the two
carriers, Comair announced Monday. The $1.8 billion deal will make
Dayton's main regional airline a subsidiary of its main major
airline. (Gaffney, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
